	<h1 class="mul-hdr-rule">{{ model.title }}</h1>
	<p>
		We've come up with a system for using grids that automatically does all the math for you. Our box-sizing: border-box is designed so that borders and padding won't affect the overall width of the columns of a grid. In a sense, our grids are fluid and user responsive and designed to work with and adapt to any type of device, screen resolution, or browser. Smaller screen resolutions, such as that of a mobile device, will display grids as stacked so content won't be distorted and lost, no matter what device our users are on. And of course, our grid design represents the Mercer name across the board. 
	</p>

	
	<!-- Unit Measures -->
